Discussed physical properties of an exciton in 2D materials, related to the interplay between 2D nonlocal screening and disorder can play a role in multiexciton configurations. For example, they can be relevant for interaction between distant 2D excitons in the above interfaces or semiconductor-based ultrathin films. Indeed, the exciton radii (around 5 nm, which is of the order of 10 lattice constants) presented in Fig. 5 are characterized by dipole moments er¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
